  A popular Lekki Pastor, Apostle Chris Omashola, who heads the Zionwealth Church, was on Saturday afternoon involved in a auto crash in Warri. His Special Assistant, Mr. Seun Adeyeye, in a terse statement, explainedÂ  the accident occurred at about 3pm around a flyover opposite Delta Mall in Warri, Delta State. Omashola, who is also a Public Relations expert, was driving alone in a Toyota Camry when the car crashed. The cleric was rushed to Skyphon Medical Centre along Refinery Road, Warri for medical attention.